📘 Pagination in Spring Data JPA (SCN)

1️⃣ Concept
Pagination = fetching data in chunks (pages) instead of loading everything at once.
👉 Improves:
Performance ⚡
Memory usage 🧠
API usability 📦

2️⃣ Approach
📌 Key Components
Component
Role
Pageable
Input (page number, size, sort)
Page<T>
Output (data + metadata)
PageRequest
Implementation of Pageable


3️⃣ Code

🔹 A. Repository
Page<ProductEntity> findAll(Pageable pageable);


🔹 B. Controller (Basic Pagination)
import org.springframework.data.domain.*;

@GetMapping("/products")
public List<ProductEntity> getProducts() {

    Pageable pageable = PageRequest.of(0, 5); // page 0, size 5

    Page<ProductEntity> page = productRepository.findAll(pageable);

    return page.getContent(); // actual data
}


🔹 C. Dynamic Pagination (Recommended)
@GetMapping("/products")
public Page<ProductEntity> getProducts(
        @RequestParam int page,
        @RequestParam int size) {

    Pageable pageable = PageRequest.of(page, size);

    return productRepository.findAll(pageable);
}


🔹 D. Pagination + Sorting
@GetMapping("/products")
public Page<ProductEntity> getProducts(
        @RequestParam int page,
        @RequestParam int size,
        @RequestParam String sortBy,
        @RequestParam String direction) {

    Sort sort = direction.equalsIgnoreCase("asc") ?
            Sort.by(sortBy).ascending() :
            Sort.by(sortBy).descending();

    Pageable pageable = PageRequest.of(page, size, sort);

    return productRepository.findAll(pageable);
}


4️⃣ Key Points
🔑 Page Numbering
Starts from 0
0 → first page
1 → second page

🔑 Important Methods (Page)
page.getContent();        // list of data
page.getTotalElements();  // total rows
page.getTotalPages();     // total pages
page.getNumber();         // current page
page.getSize();           // page size


🔑 PageRequest Syntax
PageRequest.of(pageNo, pageSize);
PageRequest.of(pageNo, pageSize, sort);


5️⃣ Learnings / Interview Insights

⭐ Why pagination?
Avoid loading large datasets ❌
Improves API scalability ✅
Used in almost every production API

⭐ Common Mistake (you faced this)
Pageable pageable = PageRequest.of(0, 5);
pageable.getContent(); ❌

✔ Correct:
Page<ProductEntity> page = repo.findAll(pageable);
page.getContent(); ✅


⭐ Best Practice
Always expose pagination via API:
/products?page=0&size=5


⭐ When to return what?
Return Type
Use Case
List<T>
Only data needed
Page<T>
Data + metadata needed


🚀 Bonus (Production Style Response)
@GetMapping("/products")
public Map<String, Object> getProducts(
        @RequestParam int page,
        @RequestParam int size) {

    Page<ProductEntity> pageData =
            productRepository.findAll(PageRequest.of(page, size));

    Map<String, Object> response = new HashMap<>();
    response.put("data", pageData.getContent());
    response.put("totalPages", pageData.getTotalPages());
    response.put("totalElements", pageData.getTotalElements());

    return response;
}


🧠 Final Summary
Pageable → request config
Page → actual paginated result
Page index starts at 0
Combine with sorting for real-world APIs


